1 WILL
2 DATE 1855
2 PLAC Tippah Co., MS
2 SOUR @S106@
3 DATA
4 TEXT The State of Mississipi
5 CONT Tippah County
5 CONT 21 May 1855
5 CONT
5 CONT In the name of God Amen, I Ford Mathis of the County of Tippah and State of Mississippi. Considering the uncertaintly of this mortal life and being of sound mind and memory blessed be Almity God for the same, do this the twenty first of May in th
5 CONC e year of our Lord one thousand Eight hundred and fifty five make and publish this my last will and testament in the manner following to wit, First I desire to be decently and privately buried in the Church Yard at Cokesberry by the side of my dep
5 CONC arted wife and to have our graves enclosed with a brick wall of good and well burnt brick about 18 inches high and of a proper thickings with palins on top of the wall with diamond heads, the palins painted white with Common plain toomstones.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I give and bequeath unto my daughter Elisabeth Bass one hundred dollars in addition to what I have heretofore Given her.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I give and bequeath unto my daughter Charlott Bass two hundred dollars in addition to what heretofore Given her.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I give and bequeath unto my son Giles Mathis two hundred and fifty dollars in addition to what I have heretofore Given him.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I give and bequeath unto my daughter Sousan [Susan] Cole three hundred and fifty dollars.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I give and bequeath unto my daughter Clara Briley, Matilda Mathis, Kitty Henson and Jula Mathis one dollar each in addition to what I have heretofore Given them.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I Give and bequeath unto my daughter Tempa Claxton Twenty dollars in addition to what I have heretofore Given her.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I give and bequeath unto my two Grandsons John Mathis and Benit Mathis one hundred and ten dollars to be equally divided between them by my executors when they arrive at the age of twenty one years and the interest that may accrue upon the ab
5 CONC ove amount of money to be only appropiated to the benefit of the children.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I give and bequeath unto my two grand daughters Sally Bass and Lucinda Bass the sum of fifty dollars each.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I give and bequeath unto Wyatt Mathis two hundred dollars for his trouble as one of my executors and for my other executors to paid reasonable compensation for his services.
5 CONT
5 CONT ALSO I give and bequeath unto the Methodist Church South twenty five dollars the benefit of the Society where I belong to be paid by my executors to the preachers that travel the Poters Creek Circuit for there support to be paid by my executors an
5 CONC uly for five years. All of the above bequeath are to be paid by my executors after they have had sufficent time to sell and collect. And I hereby direct my excutors to sell all of my propety boath real and personal at public auction on a twelve mo
5 CONC nths credit the purchaser Given note and with approved Security with the exception of my negro woman Riah. She is to have the right of selecting her master to select at least some three men for a master and then be sold at private Sale.
5 CONT
5 CONT All the rest and residue of my estate that may remain after all debts and expences to be equally divided between all my children for there only proper use and benefit. Absolutely, And I do hereby costitute and appoint Wyatt Mathis and James W. Oak
5 CONC es my Sole executors of this my last will and testament in witness whereof I have hereunto Set my hand and Seal the day and year first above written.
5 CONT
5 CONT Ford Mathis (Seal)
5 CONT
5 CONT Signed Sealed published and I declared by the testor as and for his last will and testament in our presence was at his request in his presence and in the presence of each other have Subscribe our names as witnesses thereto.
5 CONT
5 CONT S.Y. Ragan
5 CONT E.J. Stone
5 CONT
5 CONT The State of Mississippi}
5 CONT Tippah County } I Daniel Hunt Clerk of the Probate Court of said county certify that the foregoing Last Will and Testament of Ford Mathis dec'd and the Proof thereto annexed was this day recorded in Will Book H in pages 181, 2, 3, & 4.
5 CONT Given under my hand and the seal of said Court at office this 2nd July 1885
5 CONT Daniel Hunt Clk B. E. N. Hunt DC
5 CONT
