1 CONC Later in life, Polly Ann was living with her son, Jacob Benjamin when they all moved to Simla, Colorado in 1917.  Polly soon became homesick and said she didn't want to die anywhere but Missouri.  They sold their farm and took the train back to Di
1 CONC xon, Missouri.  Unfortunately, they all caught the influenza on the trip, and Polly Ann died just a few days after they arrived.
