0 @N23@ NOTE
1 CONC Jacob lived in Washington County, MD and was a soldier during the Revolutionary War.  He later moved the family to Kentucky, and in 1811 to Missouri and settled on Loutre Island in Montgomer County.  Prior to the move to Kentucky, his children ha
1 CONC d never tasted cornbread.  In 1812 he built a blockhouse for protection against indians.  During their residence here an old indian named Phillips lived with them for several years.  Phillips left them and later his body was found out in the wilde
1 CONC rness with his gun lying by his side.  Jacob died at this blockhouse in 1822.
0 @N24@ NOTE
