1 CONC William enlisted on 26 July 1862 at Centerville, Iowa.  Mustered as a private in Company G, 36th Regiment of the Iowa Infantry Volunteers at Camp Lincoln, Keokuk, Iowa on 1 Oct 1862. William contracted mumps and typhoid fever and was in hospital a
1 CONC t Memphis, TN.  Received a medical discharge as disabled on 22 Feb 1863, and was held for a time at hospital.  Long after the war, William and family went from Iowa to Nebraska by covered wagon to homestead.  In 1892, sold their homestead in Nebra
1 CONC ska and moved to Oklahoma to homestead, taking 2 covered wagons and youngest 4 kids.  Moved to where Carney, Oklahoma was founded.
