1 CONC In 1860, Harrison was living and working as a farm laborer, along with an H. Bowles, on widow Adaline Hildreth's farm.  Within two years, Harrison and Adaline were married and the firstborn twins of their marriage, William and Cassandra, had mad
1 CONC e their appearance.  Harrison was 11 years younger than Adaline, whose first husband had been 17 years than she, yielding a difference in age of 28 years between her two husbands - a full generation, and then some.
1 CONT
1 CONT The Illinois Death and Stillbirth Index for 1916 - 1947 lists Harrison's birth date as 8 Sep 1839.  However, extrapolation from census dates and his reported ages shows he was born between 21 June and 5 July 1840.  However, the 1900 census did no
1 CONC t ask for the person's age, but instead for the month and year the person was born, and Harrison reported September 1840.
1 CONT
1 CONT According to Harrison's obituary, he had four step-brothers (Jim, Allen, Elisha & George) and two step-sisters (Ellen & Louisa).  According to private family trees on Ancestry.com, there were 4 step-brothers (Elisha, James, George Washington & All
1 CONC en) and four step-sisters (Louisa, Betty E., Migata & Amy Ellen).  According to the same private family trees, Harrison's paternal grandparents were Joseph Meachum (1772-1856) and Irena Kimball (1777-1872).
